<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-31T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="891" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d891">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/7065a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-31T18:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1825. Please ascertain and report by cable as soon as possible attitude
                            of Netherlands Government towards American merchantmen defensively armed
                            which may enter Netherlands colonial ports. Such merchantmen ordinarily
                            carry a 5.40-inch gun mounted aft and a three pounder forward. Guns
                            manned by regular Navy crew of from 18 to 21 men.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>